# SYSTEM_DIRECTIVE: CONTEXT_SYSTEM

## Memory Ownership

CONTEXT/* is the only canonical mutable memory.
- TODO.md         -> current worklist, blockers, verification
- DECISIONS.md    -> durable decisions with rationale and Confidence
- ARCHITECTURE.md -> current structure snapshot
- LESSONS.md      -> preferences, corrections, pitfalls (scoped)
- handoffs/       -> one session-continuity file at a time

Ignore CLAUDE.md during normal work. Read it only for adapter repair.

## Memory Style

Telegraphic ASCII. Bullets under 12 words. Sentences under 20 words.
ASCII operators only: != == -> => in not and or, plus "blocked by", "TODO:", "RISK:".
No LaTeX, no Unicode math, no box-drawing, no em-dashes.

## Boot Read

TODO.md, DECISIONS.md, ARCHITECTURE.md.
Also LESSONS.md when preferences may matter.
Current handoff only when resuming continuity.

## Module Adapters

None yet. Create .cursor/rules/module-{name}.mdc when a subtree grows its own runtime, conventions, integration, or repeated co-edited cluster.

## Mid-Chat Re-Read

Re-read a memory file when it changed, when scope shifts, when a contradiction appears, or before edits that depend on current plan, decisions, or architecture.

## Write Triggers

- TODO.md         -> task status, order, blockers, verification change
- DECISIONS.md    -> durable direction chosen or proven by implementation
- ARCHITECTURE.md -> structure, boundaries, flows, or integrations change
- LESSONS.md      -> durable preference, correction, or pitfall emerges
- handoffs/       -> explicit end-of-session only

## End-Of-Task Sync

Update the relevant CONTEXT/* file before closing a task. Do not update adapters during routine progress.

## Do Not Write

- Do not store task state in CLAUDE.md or this rule file.
- Do not duplicate CLAUDE.md content here; the two adapters are independent.
- Do not write to LOOP/* during routine work (no LOOP/ exists in this project yet).
